#Text=Twitter via the web , in my experience , tends to use https : // connections .
#Text=Are you aware of any possibility of the government cracking such connections ?
#Text=( I 'm not up to date on the crypto arms race ) .
#Text=You do n't need to crack https , per se , to compromise its security .
#Text=See this piece about fraudulent https certificates :
#Text=Iranian hackers obtain fraudulent https — EFF website .
#Text=And , do you believe that far , far more websites should - by default - employ https : // connections to protect people 's privacy ?
#Text=We absolutely think that more websites should employ https !
#Text=Here is a guide for site operators : ( See external links , Ed . )
#Text=Birgitta Jonsdottir responds

#Text=Finally , Wikinews approached the Icelandic politician , and WikiLeaks supporter , who has made this specific case a landmark in how the U.S. Government handles dealings with – supposedly – friendly governments and their elected representatives .
#Text=A number of questions were posed , seeking the Icelandic Parliamentarian 's views :
#Text=How did you feel when you were notified the US Government wanted your Twitter account , and message , details ?
#Text=Were you shocked ?
#Text=Birgitta Jonsdottir 's Facebook profile picture .
#Text=I felt angry but not shocked .
#Text=I was expecting something like this to happen because of my involvement with WikiLeaks .
#Text=My first reaction was to tweet about it .
#Text=What do you believe is their reasoning in selecting you as a ' target ' ?
#Text=It is quite clear to me that USA authorities are after Julian Assange and will use any means possible to get even with him .
#Text=I think I am simply a pawn in a much larger context .
#Text=I did of course both act as a spokesperson for WikiLeaks in relation to the Apache video and briefly for WikiLeaks , and I put my name to the video as a co-producer .
#Text=I have not participated in any illegal activity and thus being a target does n't make me lose any sleep .

#Text=Are you concerned that , as a Member of Parliament involved in the Icelandic Modern Media Initiative ( IMMI ) , the US attempt to obtain your Twitter data is interfering with planned Icelandic government policy ?
#Text=No

#Text=In an earlier New York Times ( NYT ) article , you 're indicating there is nothing they can obtain about you that bothers you ; but , how do you react to them wanting to know everyone you talk to ?
#Text=It bothers me and according to top computer scientists the government should be required to obtain a search warrant to get our IP addresses from Twitter .

#Text=I am , though , happy I am among the people DOJ is casting their nets around because of my parliamentary immunity ; I have a greater protection then many other users and can use that immunity to raise the issue of lack of rights for those that use social media .
